Akhmetov Buys London Penthouse for $222.2 Million, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-18T23:02:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/akhmetov-buys-london-penthouse-for-222-2-million-ft-reports.html
Ukraine’s richest man Rinat Akhmetov purchased the penthouse apartment at the One Hyde Park
residential development in Knightsbridge,  London  for 136.6
million pounds ($222.2 million), making it the U.K.’s most
expensive apartment, the Financial Times reported, without
saying where it got the information. Elena Dovzhenko, a
spokeswoman for Akhmetov, confirmed that his holding company,
System Capital Management, had invested in the Knightsbridge
development, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 